    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-09-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-09-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="692"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d692">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 814.51/183.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">British Ambassador</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">British Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-09-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 30, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: With reference to the subject
                    of the Guatemalan debt, as to which I telegraphed to you on September 29th
                    giving you the views of my Government, I must thank you for the action taken by
                    you in accordance with the wishes of my Government, as set forth in your note to
                    Mr. Mitchell Innes of September 21st. I need not say that my Government deeply
                    appreciates any assistance from the Government of the United States looking to
                    the satisfaction of British claims of this nature.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">James Bryce.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
